content:
Hi,
During a routine review of our secure web gateway logs, I noticed a URL that keeps appearing across multiple user sessions and different time windows.

The URL is https://www.google.com, and what caught my attention is that it's being accessed shortly after users open certain emails.

This isn't a domain we normally interact with, and it doesn't appear in our allowlists.

Before escalating this as a potential phishing campaign, could you check whether this URL has a known malicious or suspicious reputation?
